If the function has one or more parameters, we can pass values to these parameters using function arguments.
--> Function parameters are the variable names listed in the function definition.
--> Function arguments are the real values passed to(and received by) the function.

//Code tab:
function square(number){   //here, "number" is parameter.
    return number*number;
}
console.log(square(2)); // here, "2" which is a function argument takes the place of "number" which is a function parameter.
//End

Example, We can pass the argument 2 to the sqaure function defined above using sqaure(2). This argument is received by the parameter named number in the function.